snippet: The Tigers, who have one of the highest-scoring offenses in the nation, can claim an Ivy League title for the first time since 2006.
abstract: College Football East Roundup; Princeton clinches at least a share of its first Ivy League title since 2006 and re-establishes a long if inconsistent football tradition with a 59-23 homecoming victory against Yale; other scores noted.
lead_paragraph: The Tigers, who have one of the highest-scoring offenses in the nation, can claim an Ivy League title for the first time since 2006.

headline.main: With Dominating Offense, Princeton Trounces Yale and Gains Share of Ivy Title
headline.print_headline: Princeton Trounces Yale To Earn Share of Ivy Title
